     A couple of notes about quest objects, such as the bucket you just
acquired.  First, like quest info, you are not allowed to share them
except with people in your quest party.  Some quests are designed so
that you can't even share your items with other people in your party,
an example of which might be a ring which automatically puts itself
on your finger when you pick it up and cannot be removed.  However,
this is not a terribly common set-up and when it does occur you'll
know it.
     My second point, and as important and practical as the first,
involves the availability of quest objects.  The objects in this
quest have been specially designed so as to be there whenever you
should happen to go through.  Very often, though, this is not
the case.  You may have to wait for a room to reset, which it
does with relative frequency, before you can acquire a given item,
because someone else had already taken it.  So, just becase
you don't find a certain item in a certain place doesn't mean
it isn't to be found there; it only means that it isn't there at
the moment.  You may come back later and find the item you are
looking for sitting right where you expected it to be.  Then
again, you might not.  The only way you can be sure is if you
know no one has been in the area recently.  If you see someone
else wandering around the region, you can probably assume that
he, too, is working on the quest, in which case you might consider
pooling your resources and working on it together, rather than
fighting over the same items.
